node.text:
Our founder, owner and CEO, @fawn.weaver , may be the hardest working chief executive in the industry‼️ 💯 Just call her the James Brown of spirits. 🔥 Every day this summer, she’s landing in one of America’s greatest cities to thank the owners and GMs of the restaurants, bars and hotels that have helped make Uncle Nearest the fastest-growing American whiskey brand in U.S. history 🇺🇸 (11 straight quarters of growth ⬆️ above 100% 📈)!

While Fawn is traveling the country thanking all of the business owners and managers, our Master Blender and fifth-generation Nearest Green descendant, @victoriaeadybutler , is going city to city and thanking all of our #WhiskeyFamily with sold out events, bottle signings, and killing it in the press! 🗞️

Make sure you’re following them both on Instagram as they share their adventures of love, honor, laughter and whiskey along the way. 💯

By the way, @fawn.weaver ❤️’s to eat great food 😋, so some have said her IG is part inspirational life lessons and part food and drinks blog… We just might agree… 😉🥳 Not to mention, her #SundayWithTheWeavers has become must-see IGTV. It did, after all, birth the Grown Folk Mimosa! 🥃🥂🍊

PRO-TIP: When visiting @nearestgreendistillery this summer, make sure to ask for @fawn.weaver on Saturdays and @victoriaeadybutler on Sundays as there is a very good chance one of them will be there…AND…signing bottles! 🎤

node.text:
LESS THAN ONE WEEK LEFT #Whiskeyfamily!!! ⏰ Our 2021 #HonorYourLegacy Cocktail Competition entries are due next Monday, July 19th 2021 by 11:59pm PT, so if you’re a bartender planning to enter, now’s the time! A trip to Nearest Green Distillery to make your cocktail for @fawn.weaver and @victoriaeadybutler is on the line 🔥 along with the opportunity to have your drink featured on the menu of Humble Barron at Nearest Green Distillery. You DO NOT want to miss this opportunity! See link in bio for the rules and details. 

And speaking of the competition, the killer cocktail pictured above comes from one of our 2020 #HonorYourLegacy winners, @melodieciji . Featuring Uncle Nearest 1884 🥃, grilled peaches 🍑 and ginger, it might be called Last Day of Summer, but it’s one we’ll be sipping all summer long! 

Last Day of Summer

Ingredients:

2oz Uncle Nearest 1884 Whiskey
1.5 oz fresh lime juice
1.5 oz grilled peach and ginger syrup
3 dashes Black walnut bitters
One small slice of peach

Grilled Peach and Ginger Syrup:

-2 sliced peaches grilled. I used cast iron grill pan, 4 dashes of liquid smoke and 2 drops of vanilla extract. Grilled peaches until nicely caramelized. 
-Roughly 2 inches of peeled and sliced fresh ginger root. Muddled in the sugar to release some
of the juices
1 cup water
1 cup sugar
Boil and simmer until desired flavor infusion. Set aside and let cool.

Method:

Add all liquid ingredients to a cocktail shaker with ice. Shake vigorously for 8-10 seconds. Double strain into a chilled coupe glass.
Garnish with a fresh peach slice.

WHAT A CELEBRATION WE HAD‼️🎉  Thank you #whiskeyfamily for coming out to be a part of this moment in history. For those of you who couldn't join us, we can't wait to see you in Shelbyville soon! Here's a little peak of the events from our Nearest Green Distillery Phase 2 opening on 06.19.21. The 10 photo limit really can't do it justice! 📸
⁣
From the moment everyone walked into the newly unveiled Welcome Center, they knew this distillery was unlike any other. On display in the first foyer is the original millstone and artifacts from Distillery No. 7, where Nearest Green was head stiller in the 19th century. In the second foyer, commissioned oil paintings from the incomparable @raybonillapainter of 8 of Nearest Green's children and grandchildren. flanking both walls. Then there's the narrative walls of Tennessee Whiskey, Tennessee Walking Horses & Tennessee Music followed by an insane amount of Uncle Nearest retail, which leads to the world's first non-alcoholic speakeasy, Philo+Frank, _The_Barrel_House, the @kelseymontagueart #WhatLiftsUs Angel Wings, then onto our first single-story rickhouse, our Family Tasting Room, Master Blender House and so much more! Y’all, we did a thing in Phase Two!⁣
⁣
As this was also the celebration of Juneteenth (and the first year that it was recognized as a national holiday), there was so much life and energy to take in around every corner of the distillery. People laughed, sang, cried happy tears, danced and embraced one another. 🕺🏽💃🏽 Everyone present could feel that this was truly a MOVEMENT, not a MOMENT.💪🏽
   ⁣
Thank you to the more than 50 TN state Congressmen, House Representatives, Senators, Mayors, County Commissioners — and the Black Caucus who rolled in 26 deep — that came out to celebrate with us. WHAT AN HONOR!⁣
⁣
For those that were not able to attend thank you for joining us virtually on IGTV. We know y'all were with us in spirit!❤️ Thanks to our whiskey family for the huge support and to our amazing Uncle Nearest team for bringing this vision to life! ⁣

PHOTO CREDIT: @stacyprestonphotography @cfatke 
@karafayephotography @aussiebarcat 
  ⁣
#morethanwhiskey #unclenearest #nearestgreendistillery #juneteenth

ANOTHER EPIC ANNOUNCEMENT‼️

From Day One, Uncle Nearest has been a purpose-driven company, and we continue to double down on that. ❤️ We are #MoreThanWhiskey.

“On June 1, 1921, an entire community of wealthy and successful African Americans was wiped out in a matter of hours. We are talking about 35 square blocks known as Black Wall Street,” said Fawn Weaver, @fawn.weaver CEO of Uncle Nearest Premium Whiskey. “As an African American, learning about that history broke my heart because we, as a people, were really onto something in Tulsa, Oklahoma. We were lifting one another up and creating wealth within our own community and then showing others how to do it for themselves. 🇺🇸🤝🏽 The amount lost was ~$2M, the equivalent of ~$26.7M in today’s money.” 😮 

“It is no coincidence the amount of the Fund is nearly double that and the amount invested in the first two Black-founded spirit brands in the Fund, is $2M each. 💰We cannot go back and undo the past, but I do believe we have full power over our future, and that recreating a Black Wall Street of sorts within the spirits industry is a great place to start.” ✊🏽🥃💯 (Link in Bio)

SCROLL RIGHT ➡️ #WHISKEYFAMILY to see how we are continuing to change the game and make it more inclusive for all. 👍🏽

#UncleNearest #PurposeDriven #WeAreAllAmbassadors #TogetherWeRise

THIS. IS. EPIC‼️
 
What is better than one Trilogy drop? NINE. Happening all at the same time, on the same day… @nearestgreendistillery . 🤯🥳 YES! YOU HEARD IT RIGHT!
 
We know many of you were disappointed the tours for opening weekend sold out so fast! BUT…just know…there are still plenty of reasons to come celebrate with us on Saturday, June 19, 2021. And at the TOP of that list (DRUMROLL, PLEASE 🥁):
 
THE INAUGURAL MASTER BLEND (MBE) TRILOGY DROP
 
In 2017, when we began putting our own whiskey into barrels (made with Tennessee grown organic corn, by the way 😉), folks weren’t even sure our brand had “legs.” NOW, four years later, THIS IS THE MOMENT 160 years in the making. 💯🔥We are SO proud of the liquid gold releasing out of OUR barrels right now.❤️
 
That brings us to our MASTER BLEND. For the past year, @victoriaeadybutler has been setting aside every barrel she tasted and thought was OFF THE CHARTS AMAZING. Blending the two together proved masterful! 🤩
 
Bottled at Barrel Strength, she’s created 4 MBEs, that will ALL drop on June 19th, a combination of our 1884 at barrel strength and our liquid gold four years in the making.
 
Blend No. 001 | Proof: 111.02
Blend No. 002 | Proof: 114
Blend No. 003 | Proof 113.4
Blend No. 004 | Proof 111.11
 
Although we’re just announcing this to the world…we’ve been entering it into competitions since last year. 🤫 We’re PROUD TO ANNOUNCE our Master Blend Edition already won DOUBLE GOLD at the San Francisco World Spirits Competition, DOUBLE GOLD at the SIP Awards and DOUBLE PLATINUM at @fredminnick ‘s Ascot Awards. 🏆 ALL these competitions were blind taste tested. 🎤💥
 
Sales will be limited to one (1) Master Blend Trilogy per person and one (1) 1820 Single Barrel Trilogy per person. Speaking of which, we’re also dropping five (yes, you read that right – FIVE) 1820 Single Barrel Trilogies: US-50, US-52, US-53, US-59, and US-62.
 
Meet us June 19, 2021 at 9AM for our Ribbon Cutting, enjoy a #GrownFolkMimosa with @fawn.weaver , then follow Victoria over to her Master Blender House, where the Trilogies…will OFFICIALLY DROP. 🙌🏽 🥃
 
#morethanwhiskey #unclenearest #nearestgreendistillery

IF YOU DON’T ALREADY KNOW who this whiskey industry powerhouse 💪🏽 is, you’ll want to learn more about her, #whiskeyfamily! Our very own Sherrie Moore, Director of Whiskey Operations for Uncle Nearest, was the FIRST woman to oversee operations at a major American whiskey brand.🥇 A member of the Motlow family in Lynchburg, making Tennessee Whiskey has always been her roots. And as the former Treasurer of the American Filtration Society, if you want to know who is responsible for our unique Triple Filtration process, it’s our residential whiskey nerd, Sherrie Moore. 🙌🏽

Sherrie was breaking glass ceilings back in the 70’s, when women in whiskey operation leadership roles were nonexistent. She spent over 31 years in the family business, Jack Daniel Distillery, and brought that incredible wealth of knowledge to Uncle Nearest. She worked alongside descendants of Nearest Green her entire life, and is lifelong friends with our Master Blender, @victoriaeadybutler Victoria Eady Butler. FUN FACT: Many don't know this, but Sherrie was the one who first said to Fawn, “If you decide to honor Nearest with a bottle, I will come out of retirement to make sure you get it right.” Sherrie did just that and helped Fawn and our incredible operations team to propel this brand to the Most Awarded American Whiskey (including Bourbon, of course) of 2019, 2020 and we're already coming in hot on the awards in 2021. Thank you for everything you do, Ms. Sherrie! ❤️💯🏆

DO YOU KNOW WHAT TOMORROW IS #WHISKEYFAMILY?? Cinco de Mayo 🇲🇽 While we all LOVE our whiskey, 🥃 who doesn’t appreciate a great margarita once in a while? So we got to thinking…why should tequila have all the fun? 🤔

This year, we asked our incredibly talented Uncle Nearest team to send us their best “whiskey margarita” recipes for a little competition and they did not disappoint! 🙌🏽There were many delicious contenders, but “The Ngoma Coma” from @schwabgregory came out on top! This recipe is a snap to make, goes great with tacos 🌮and is oh so delicious! Bet you can’t drink just one!!

Fun fact: The word “gnoma” comes from East Africa and means: a night of music and dancing 💃🏽🎶🕺🏽

The Ngoma Coma

1.5 oz Uncle Nearest 1856
1.0 oz Fresh lime juice
1/2 oz Agave Syrup (see below)
1/4 oz Fresh squeezed OJ

For agave syrup, combine equal parts agave nectar and warm water. Stir until combined. Cool.

METHOD
Shake all ingredients with ice together vigorously, strain over salted glass in fresh ice and lime wheel
